sleepcountry wrote:(Just the other day I was reading about a letter from the 50s that a 12-year old kid wrote asking Frank Lloyd Wright to design a doghouse for his dog Eddie. Surprisingly, Lloyd Wright actually drew up a plan for a super cool doghouse. Just because a guy is dead sure doesn't mean it's not worth finding out more about him.)Frank Lloyd Wright also designed a house for a Purdue professor and his wife in the 1950s. They commissioned Wright to design them a home by calling him up on the phone. They couldn't afford his usual rates, nor could they afford to outfit the home with all the furniture and other accoutrements Wright created as part of the design. Wright did all the design work for a budget they could afford, in exchange for a promise that they would have it built and furnished as Wright had envisioned.http://www.samara-house.org/welcome.htm
